  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop the<strong> sweet potatoes</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato wedges</strong> to a tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 12-15 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are cooking, peel and slice a few rounds off the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining red onion</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2258Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>turkey mince</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>,<strong> grated onion</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a large bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands are the best way!)<strong> </strong>– this is your<strong> herby turkey mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654612881697-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
